Designates a method to be used when obtaining the DB connection from the DB connection pool when using a framework or a proprietary connection pool created in the application.

The method configured by db_connection_get must return java.sql.Connection.

    db.DBConnectionManager getConnection

When configuring this method, the [enable_sql_pointcut](./agentHelp?type=1&key=enable_sql_pointcut) option should be set to false (to prevent redundant tracking).

---

* Default value: None
* Type: string (able to configure multiple settings using the line change).
* Sample value

        db.DBManager getConnection
        db.DBConnectionManager getConnection

* Restart: Required
* Related options
    * [db_connection_close](./agentHelp?key=db_connection_close&type=1)
    * [enable_jdbc_bootstrap_wrapper_factory](./agentHelp?key=enable_jdbc_bootstrap_wrapper_factory&type=1)
* Supported version: 5.0.0